00:40:26,143 --> 00:40:27,143
CHAPTER SIX
Nancy Wake

565
00:40:27,143 --> 00:40:28,143
c. 1912 - 2011

566
00:40:28,143 --> 00:40:29,143
The woman who became a spy in the Second World
War

567
00:40:29,143 --> 00:40:30,143
I fought with the French Resistance against
the Germans in the Second World War.

568
00:40:30,143 --> 00:40:31,143
I got weapons for the Resistance fighters
and helped fighters to escape.

569
00:40:31,143 --> 00:40:38,829
I was part of the final victory against the
Germans in 1945.

570
00:40:38,829 --> 00:40:44,170
I was born in New Zealand, but I grew up in
Sydney, Australia.

571
00:40:44,170 --> 00:40:53,319
When I was 16 years old, I left home and got
a job as a nurse in the Australian countryside.

572
00:40:53,319 --> 00:41:02,190
In 1932, I received a surprise - 200 pounds
from my aunt.

573
00:41:02,190 --> 00:41:07,760
It was a lot of money at that time and I decided
to spend it.

574
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:14,010
I went to Sydney Harbour and bought a ticket
to North America.

575
00:41:14,010 --> 00:41:24,930
I enjoyed the journey on the ship and then
travelled around the USA and Canada.

576
00:41:24,930 --> 00:41:30,130
When I wasn't travelling, I worked as a waitress
to earn some money.

577
00:41:30,130 --> 00:41:35,349
After a while, I moved to Britain.

578
00:41:35,349 --> 00:41:43,960
I wanted to work on a newspaper, so I studied
to become a newspaper reporter.

579
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:50,940
I got my first job on a newspaper in Paris,
where I learned to speak French.

580
00:41:50,940 --> 00:41:57,480
I went to Germany and Austria for the newspaper.

581
00:41:57,480 --> 00:42:04,540
I saw the terrible things that Adolf Hitler
and his Nazi party were doing in their country.

582
00:42:04,540 --> 00:42:09,089
I realized then that the Nazis were very dangerous.

583
00:42:09,089 --> 00:42:13,680
And they wanted to rule the whole of Europe.

584
00:42:13,680 --> 00:42:14,680
***

585
00:42:14,680 --> 00:42:22,660
In 1940, the Germans attacked France and occupied
most of the country.

586
00:42:22,660 --> 00:42:30,049
I was already living in the south of France,
where I married my first husband, a businessman,

587
00:42:30,049 --> 00:42:31,900
Henri Fiocca.

588
00:42:31,900 --> 00:42:37,680
We both hated the Nazis and wanted to help
in the war against them.

589
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:42,170
I began to work for the French Resistance
in Marseille.

590
00:42:42,170 --> 00:42:51,680
I delivered secret messages to the Resistance
fighters and I also helped fighters to escape.

591
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:54,650
The Germans tried to catch me.

592
00:42:54,650 --> 00:43:02,230
I used false papers and changed my appearance
so they didn't recognize me.

593
00:43:02,230 --> 00:43:09,349
In 1943, the Germans caught me, but luckily
I escaped.

594
00:43:09,349 --> 00:43:12,700
It was too dangerous for me to stay in France.

595
00:43:12,700 --> 00:43:20,730
I had to leave my husband and go over the
Pyrenees mountains to Spain.

596
00:43:20,730 --> 00:43:27,630
From Spain, I escaped to London and joined
the British army.

597
00:43:27,630 --> 00:43:32,980
I was a little surprised when the British
wanted me to become a spy.

598
00:43:32,980 --> 00:43:40,480
They wanted me to be part of a secret army,
which helped the French Resistance.

599
00:43:40,480 --> 00:43:46,789
The training with the British army was very
hard and I worked night and day to learn the

600
00:43:46,789 --> 00:43:49,160
special skills.

601
00:43:49,160 --> 00:43:53,940
I learned how to look after injured fighters.

602
00:43:53,940 --> 00:43:56,660
I also learned to kill.

603
00:43:56,660 --> 00:44:06,460
And so I became a spy and set off on my first
mission to France.

604
00:44:06,460 --> 00:44:07,460
***

605
00:44:07,460 --> 00:44:12,190
I arrived in France on 29th April 1944.

606
00:44:12,190 --> 00:44:18,870
At first, the French Resistance didn't believe
that I could help them.

607
00:44:18,870 --> 00:44:21,980
They didn't think that a woman could be a
fighter.

608
00:44:21,980 --> 00:44:29,030
A Resistance leader told one of his men, 'This
woman could be an enemy.

609
00:44:29,030 --> 00:44:33,099
Ask her to go for a walk with you.

610
00:44:33,099 --> 00:44:37,710
When no one is around, kill her!'

611
00:44:37,710 --> 00:44:40,980
They didn't realize I could speak French.

612
00:44:40,980 --> 00:44:45,339
I understood everything.

613
00:44:45,339 --> 00:44:53,080
When we went for the walk, I told the man,
'If you attack me, I will kill you first.'

614
00:44:53,080 --> 00:44:59,349
He believed me and took me back to the camp.

615
00:44:59,349 --> 00:45:04,220
At last, the Resistance allowed me to join
them.

616
00:45:04,220 --> 00:45:11,630
I got weapons from Britain and also took part
in their attacks against the Germans.

617
00:45:11,630 --> 00:45:16,500
We blew up railway lines and stole German
weapons.

618
00:45:16,500 --> 00:45:22,420
On one occasion, I killed a German soldier.

619
00:45:22,420 --> 00:45:31,859
On another, I killed a Resistance fighter
who was working for the Germans.

620
00:45:31,859 --> 00:45:32,859
***

621
00:45:32,859 --> 00:45:38,700
Our attacks against the Germans were very
successful, but it was difficult to keep everything

622
00:45:38,700 --> 00:45:41,210
secret.

623
00:45:41,210 --> 00:45:47,890
Many local people were frightened of the German
soldiers and sometimes they gave the Germans

624
00:45:47,890 --> 00:45:51,329
information about our plans.

625
00:45:51,329 --> 00:45:58,910
On one occasion, someone told the Germans
about our secret radio transmitter.

626
00:45:58,910 --> 00:46:08,079
Our radio operator destroyed our codes so
the Germans didn't discover our secrets.

627
00:46:08,079 --> 00:46:15,380
I cycled 500 kilometres to get new codes.

628
00:46:15,380 --> 00:46:25,950
When German soldiers stopped me, I told them,
'I'm going to visit my aunt who's very ill.'

629
00:46:25,950 --> 00:46:30,549
After three days, I got the codes.

630
00:46:30,549 --> 00:46:36,109
Everyone said that I was very brave, but I
didn't think about that.

631
00:46:36,109 --> 00:46:37,850
I had to do it.

632
00:46:37,850 --> 00:46:41,329
It was part of my job.

633
00:46:41,329 --> 00:46:47,950
With the new codes, I could send secret messages
to Britain.

634
00:46:47,950 --> 00:46:52,280
We could receive new weapons and start our
attacks again.

635
00:46:52,280 --> 00:46:56,430
Our attacks were important.

636
00:46:56,430 --> 00:47:02,700
They stopped the progress of around 50,000
German soldiers.

637
00:47:02,700 --> 00:47:10,999
These soldiers weren't able to fight the British
army, which was arriving in the north of France.

638
00:47:10,999 --> 00:47:11,999
***

639
00:47:11,999 --> 00:47:19,050
In September 1944, I received orders to go
to Paris.

640
00:47:19,050 --> 00:47:27,570
In Paris, I helped the British and French
armies in the final months of the war.

641
00:47:27,570 --> 00:47:34,599
On 8th May 1945, we heard the wonderful news.

642
00:47:34,599 --> 00:47:40,680
The war was over and the victory was ours!

643
00:47:40,680 --> 00:47:44,650
I wanted to return home to my husband.

644
00:47:44,650 --> 00:47:49,040
I was shocked to discover that he was dead.

645
00:47:49,040 --> 00:47:55,260
He was killed by the Germans in 1943.

646
00:47:55,260 --> 00:48:01,200
It was time for me to start a new life.

647
00:48:01,200 --> 00:48:06,849
I went back to Australia and tried to become
a politician.

648
00:48:06,849 --> 00:48:13,869
I wasn't successful and life seemed boring
after the war.

649
00:48:13,869 --> 00:48:21,269
I then moved to the UK for several years and
I got an office job with the British secret

650
00:48:21,269 --> 00:48:23,640
service.

651
00:48:23,640 --> 00:48:30,069
I was happy to receive many honours for my
work in the war, such as the George Medal

652
00:48:30,069 --> 00:48:33,190
from the British.

653
00:48:33,190 --> 00:48:40,380
And at the end of my life, I felt proud to
be part of one of the most important victories

654
00:48:40,380 --> 00:48:41,380
in history.

655
00:48:41,380 --> 00:48:46,681
The victory brought peace and freedom to Europe.

656
00:48:46,681 --> 00:48:47,681
